    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by heightened operational readiness and strategic focus on the Pacific theater. Carrier strike groups USS Theodore Roosevelt and USS Nimitz are actively deployed in the Pacific, with the former leading RIMPAC 2026 exercises and the latter conducting sustained operations in the Philippine Sea. This aligns with a broader emphasis on multilateral exercises and regional deterrence, particularly in response to Chinese maritime assertiveness. The USS John F. Kennedy remains in port for final construction, indicating ongoing modernization efforts. Air activity is dominated by training missions, with advanced tactical training observed in the central and western U.S., alongside high-altitude ISR operations in key regions like San Diego and the South Pacific. Notable maritime patrol activity is concentrated in the Gulf of Mexico, Philippine Sea, and near the UK, suggesting persistent surveillance and readiness operations. The data indicates no immediate escalation but underscores a strategic shift toward rapid deployment capabilities and sustained presence in the Pacific, with a secondary focus on European and Atlantic theaters. The absence of significant Atlantic deployments suggests a prioritization of Pacific stability amid regional tensions.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
